 
9. Shape Calculator for Architects üèóÔ∏è
Scenario: Architects need a tool for shape area calculations.
 Tasks:
Create a constructor function Shape(type).


Create constructor functions Circle(radius) and Rectangle(width, height), reusing Shape.


Use prototype to define getArea() for each shape.


Create instances and log area using getArea().



10. E-Commerce Product Management System üõí
Scenario: You're designing a backend for an e-commerce system.
 Tasks:
Create a constructor function ECommerceProduct(name, price, category).


Add methods using prototype: applyDiscount(percent) and checkStock(stock).


Create a constructor ElectronicsProduct(name, price, category, warrantyPeriod) that builds on ECommerceProduct.


Override applyDiscount to apply extra discount for electronics.


